  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "WAREHOUSE ASSISTANT",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Receive, inspect, and store raw materials and components used in the manufacturing process</p></li><li><p>Pick, pack, and dispatch finished products according to production schedules and customer orders</p></li><li><p>Maintain accurate inventory records and update stock levels in the warehouse management system</p></li><li><p>Assist in the preparation and packaging of products for shipping</p></li><li><p>Operate forklifts and other warehouse equipment to move materials and products safely</p></li><li><p>Conduct regular inventory audits and cycle counts to ensure inventory accuracy</p></li><li><p>Maintain a clean and organized warehouse environment, ensuring compliance with safety regulations</p></li><li><p>Collaborate with production and logistics teams to ensure timely delivery of materials and products</p></li><li><p>Report any discrepancies or damages in shipments to the warehouse supervisor</p></li></ul><p><strong>Skills:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Proficiency in warehouse management software and MS Office</p></li><li><p>Excellent organizational and time management skills</p></li><li><p>Strong attention to detail and accuracy</p></li><li><p>Ability to operate forklifts and other warehouse equipment</p></li><li><p>Understanding of manufacturing processes and materials handling<br /><br /><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p><ul><li><p>High school diploma or equivalent</p></li><li><p>Proven experience as a warehouse assistant or in a similar role within the manufacturing industry</p></li><li><p>Minimum 2 years of experience in warehouse operations</p></li><li><p>Forklift certification preferred</p></li></ul></li></ul>",
